sub_title: Budget Analyst at Embassy of the United States of America
summary:
I like to study new things. Being knowledgeable about any subject is an ongoing process, and I’m always proactive about seeking new opportunities to develop and grow in my role. Those opportunities could be in the form of training, a conference, listening to a speaker, or taking on a new project, but the motivation is to increase my knowledge of the field.

Areas of expertise:
• Task oriented
• Customer Service
• Data Entry
• Computer Applications
• Stock control
• Warehouse management
• Inventory management
• Handling domestic and international shipments.

My skills: 
• Quick learner
• Problem solving under stress
• Able to work independently
• Strong attention to detail
• Knowledge of the latest warehouse procedures, equipment, and software.
